To fix the issue, we identified that a glowstone entity wasn't properly registered. Here's the patch:

```java
diff --git a/src/main/java/net/glowstone/entity/EntityTypes.java b/src/main/java/net/glowstone/entity/EntityTypes.java
index abcdef1..1234567 100644
--- a/src/main/java/net/glowstone/entity/EntityTypes.java
+++ b/src/main/java/net/glowstone/entity/EntityTypes.java
@@ -100,6 +100,8 @@ public final class EntityTypes {
         registerEntityType(EntityType.GLOW_SQUID, GlowSquid.class, true);
         registerEntityType(EntityType.POLAR_BEAR, PolarBear.class, true);
         registerEntityType(EntityType.SHULKER, Shulker.class, true);
+        // Add glowstone specific entity
+        registerEntityType(EntityType.GLLOWSTONE_ENTITY, GlowstoneEntity.class, true);
     }
 
     private static void registerEntityType(final EntityType type, final Class<? extends Entity> clazz,
```

This patch adds the missing glowstone entity registration, ensuring it spawns correctly.